<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-3184] Throwing in PDType1Font.encode for chars above 255 is wrong.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3184</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Chars like `&apos;\u2019&apos;` can be handled by the code following the test, so throwing in `PDType1Font.encode` whenever `unicode &amp;gt; 0xff` is wrong. See&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/a/34598915/581205&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/a/34598915/581205&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
