                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="15085732" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 6 Jan 2016 16:06:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are using one of the 14 standard fonts and their encoding is limited to 8 bit codes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can&apos;t encode U+2019 in font Helvetica. Type 1 fonts only support 8-bit code points&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have to follow the WinAnsiEncoding as described in the PDF spec. Use U+0092 instead of U+2019 and everything should work fine. &lt;br/&gt;
Alternatively you can embbed a font using PDType0Font, which supports unicode encoding (as long as the used fonts supports the characters you are using)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15085778" author="maaartinus" created="Wed, 6 Jan 2016 16:33:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So you&apos;re saying it&apos;s not a bug? I&apos;m a real n00b here, feel free to close this issue if you&apos;re sure it works correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15085970" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 6 Jan 2016 18:11:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Set to closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=maaartinus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;maaartinus&quot;&gt;maaartinus&lt;/a&gt; Please contact our &lt;a href=&quot;http://pdfbox.apache.org/mailinglists.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;mailing list&lt;/a&gt; for further questions&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15090658" author="jira-bot" created="Sat, 9 Jan 2016 15:20:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1723858 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1723858&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1723858&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3184&quot; title=&quot;Throwing in PDType1Font.encode for chars above 255 is wrong.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3184&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3184&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: remove wrong range check&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15090661" author="lehmi" created="Sat, 9 Jan 2016 15:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve doublechecked the given use case and came to the conclusion that the range check is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We compared apples and oranges. PDFont#encode expects unicode code points and the range check valid for encoding specific codes (in this case WinAnsiEncoding). This works for a lot of character but not for all&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;bullet&quot; maps to \u+2022 (unicode) and \u+0095 (WinAnsiEncoding)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Furthermore the first test isn&apos;t necessary at all as a second one follows. The codepoint is tranfered to a name using GlyphList and if the name isn&apos;t valid for the given encoding an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the confusion and thanks for the report&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16726645" author="gautam@ainosoft.com" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2018 10:50:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; shoul this issue be reopened in light of your new conclusion ?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16726653" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2018 10:59:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gautam%40ainosoft.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gautam@ainosoft.com&quot;&gt;gautam@ainosoft.com&lt;/a&gt; There is no new conclusion. My last comment is nearly 3 years old and it was fixed at the same time, see the SVN comment just above my last one. Saying that IMHO there isn&apos;t any reason for reopening this ticket or better creating a new new one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
